Package com.cafean.client.analysis

Class OwnershipManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.client.analysis.OwnershipManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ModelElement
    public class OwnershipManager
extends java.lang.Object
implements ModelElement
    The base class for an ownership and permissions manager object. This object is used by PropertySet and the ModelEditor property views to determine which objects and/or attributes can be edited by the current user. Custom, plug-in specific editors may support this feature by calling the various canWrite and setOwner methods at appropriate times.
    See Also:
    AbstractModel.getOwnershipManager(), ALOwnership, OwnedObject

    • Method Detail

      • isOwnedObjectSupported

        public boolean isOwnedObjectSupported()
        Returns true if this ownership manager supports ownership via the OwnedObject interface. The default implementation simply returns false.
        Returns:
        true if owned object is supported.

      • isALOwnershipSupported

        public boolean isALOwnershipSupported()
        Returns true if this ownership manager supports attribute level ownership via ALOwnership objects in each AbstractComponent. The default implementation simply returns false.
        Returns:
        false by default.

      • isOwnerAssignmentSupported

        public boolean isOwnerAssignmentSupported()
        Returns true if this ownership manager supports specifying an owner other than the current user for a given object. The Property View uses this method to determine if the pop-up ownership editor will be available. If so, getAvailableUsers() will be used to determine the available users in the editor.

      • setOwner

        public boolean setOwner​(OwnedObject object,
                        java.lang.String userID)
        Requests that the given user be given ownership of the given object.

        Note: Permission does not imply that the owner was changed, only that the operation is permitted. Plug-in specific ownerManager implementations may decide this as necessary.

        This base implementation simply returns false

        Parameters:
        object - the OwnedObject of which to change ownership
        userID - a String containing the userid to set
        Returns:
        true if the operation is permitted; false otherwise.

      • objectModified

        public void objectModified​(OwnedObject object,
                           java.lang.String userID)
        Notifies the ownership manager that the given object was modified by the given user.

        This implementation simply calls setOwner(com.cafean.client.analysis.OwnedObject, java.lang.String) Extensions may assume that the given user has proper permissions as this method will be called after the modification.

        Parameters:
        object - the OwnedObject that was modified
        userID - a String containing the userid of the user that modified the object
        Since:
        1.0.2

      • canRemove

        public boolean canRemove​(AbstractComponent component,
                         java.lang.String userID)
        Returns true if the given user can remove the given component. This base implementation returns true if the object not an owned object or it has no owner or the given user is the owner.
        Parameters:
        component - the AbstractComponent being removed
        userID - a String containing the user ID of the user requesting removal.
        Returns:
        true if the user can remove the given component

      • canWrite

        public boolean canWrite​(OwnedObject object,
                        java.lang.String userID)
        Returns true if the given user can write to (edit) the given object. This base implementation returns true if the object is unowned or is owned by the given user.
        Parameters:
        object - the OwnedObject to check permissions for
        userID - a String containing the user id of the user for which to check permissions
        Returns:
        true if the operation is permitted; false otherwise.

      • getCurrentUser

        public java.lang.String getCurrentUser()
        returns the userID of the current system user. This base implementation returns System.getProperty("user.name")

        Manager implementations that allow the current user to be changed may override this method to allow the default implementations to use the altered user id rather than the system property "user.name".

        Returns:
        a String containing the current user id.
        Since:
        1.1.1
